### >>>> Xavier Prudent (TU-Dresden), 9th March 2010

### >>>> This input file provides an example for the optimization of the proposal width for Markov chain.

### >>>> Detailled description of the process can be found there:
### >>>> https://atlas-wiki1.physik.uni-bonn.de/mediawiki/index.php/HowTo%27s#Optimization_of_proposal_width_for_Markov_chains

### >>>> This example uses LHC observables to mSUGRA benchmark point SPS 1a for 1 fb-1
### >>>> It is a well-constrained scenario that should cause problems (instabilities, divergence...)

### >>>> For questions or remarks, write to prudent@physik.tu-dresden.de

