################################################################################
### Parameters                                                               ###
################################################################################

### mSUGRA parameters at SPS 1a

fixParameter alphaem     127.925      GeV
fixParameter G_F           1.16637E-5
fixParameter alphas        0.1176     GeV
fixParameter massZ        91.1875     GeV
fixParameter massBottom    4.20       GeV
fixParameter massTop     172.4        GeV
fixParameter massTau       1.77684    GeV
fixParameter SignMu        1


### >>>> Here are written the starting points/widths for the Markov chain 
### >>>> Take care, for low energy observables and high-dimensionnal spaces, 
### >>>> optimization may depend on the starting point chosen (check for different values)

fitParameter M0          100          GeV +-  1.  GeV
fitParameter M12         250          GeV +-  2.5 GeV
fitParameter A0         -100          GeV +- 10.  GeV
fitParameter TanBeta      10              +-  1.

################################################################################
### Switches                                                                 ###
################################################################################

fitModel                       mSUGRA
Calculator                     SPHENO ./SPheno


### >>>> Change the link to the interface file
### >>>> Check that the interface file is empty
UseMarkovChains                on
MarkovInterfaceFilePath        /afs/blabla.de/myFittinoDirectory/interfaceFile_exampleOfIndividualOptimization.txt


### >>>> Parameters for optimizing the width of the parameter "A0"
### >>>> Optimization can last more than 8h, split your jobs among the parameters

WidthOptimization               on
NumberOptimizationSteps         1000
AcceptanceRangeUpper            0.52
AcceptanceRangeLower            0.48
IndividuallyOptimized           A0
GlobalOptimizationOnly          off
